🔥 3. Mock Interview Questions + Answers
❓ Q1: What is exit code 137?

👉 Answer:
Exit code 137 means the container was killed using SIGKILL, usually due to OOMKilled when it exceeds its memory limit.

❓ Q2: Difference between 137 and 143?

👉 Answer:

137 → Force kill (OOM or manual SIGKILL)
143 → Graceful shutdown (SIGTERM)
❓ Q3: Pod is in CrashLoopBackOff. What will you do?

👉 Answer:

Check pod status (kubectl get pods)
Describe pod (kubectl describe pod)
Check logs (kubectl logs --previous)
Identify exit code
Fix based on root cause
❓ Q4: How to fix OOMKilled?

👉 Answer:

Increase memory limits
Optimize application memory usage
Tune JVM/heap if Java app
❓ Q5: Container exits with code 127. Why?

👉 Answer:
Command not found — either wrong image or incorrect command specified.

